{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The CNN-LSTM architectures Aljaloud et al (2022); Chen et al (2022); Duru et al (2021); Li et al (2022); Liu et al (2023); Xiong et al (2022) have achieved a high accuracy of more than 70.25% and up to 91%, and on average 85.89%, except in Song et al (2020) which has achieved an accuracy of about 61% (See Figure 7).",
    "Other architectures include combining DNNs with CNN, where CNN is designed to capture spatial features in input data such as student demographic or academic records, which can then be fed into DNNs to model the temporal dependencies in the data, Sikder et al (2022) applied DNN-CNN and achieved a high accuracy of about 97%.",
    "Furthermore, combining DNNs with either LSTM Hien et al (2020); Prabowo et al (2021) or GRU Liu et al (2022c) can be an effective method for predicting student performance.",
    "For the DNNs/GRU hybrid model, GRU is used to model the temporal dependencies by extracting the temporal behavior data from the learning Fig. 7 The CNN-LSTM model's accuracy.",
    "behavior of students with the help of an attention mechanism, then DNNs are used for further processing the output of the GRU and produce the final prediction Liu et al (2022c), which has achieved an accuracy of about 92.5%."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The CNN-LSTM architectures Aljaloud et al (2022); Chen et al (2022); Duru et al (2021); Li et al (2022); Liu et al (2023); Xiong et al (2022) have achieved a high accuracy of more than 70.25% and up to 91%, and on average 85.89%, except in Song et al (2020) which has achieved an accuracy of about 61% (See Figure 7).",
    "Other architectures include combining DNNs with CNN, where CNN is designed to capture spatial features in input data such as student demographic or academic records, which can then be fed into DNNs to model the temporal dependencies in the data, Sikder et al (2022) applied DNN-CNN and achieved a high accuracy of about 97%.",
    "Furthermore, combining DNNs with either LSTM Hien et al (2020); Prabowo et al (2021) or GRU Liu et al (2022c) can be an effective method for predicting student performance.",
    "behavior of students with the help of an attention mechanism, then DNNs are used for further processing the output of the GRU and produce the final prediction Liu et al (2022c), which has achieved an accuracy of about 92.5%."
